  "rationale": "<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice B is correct. The equation of a circle in the <em>xy</em>-plane can be written as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y minus k right parenthesis squared equals r squared\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, where the center of the circle is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis h comma k right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>)</mo></math> and the radius of the circle is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math>. It&rsquo;s given that this circle has a center at <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis 16 comma 17 right parenthesis\"><mo>(</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>)</mo></math> and a radius of <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"7 k\"><mn>7</mn><mi>k</mi></math>. Substituting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"16\"><mn>16</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"h\"><mi>h</mi></math>, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"17\"><mn>17</mn></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"k\"><mi>k</mi></math>, and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"7 k\"><mn>7</mn><mi>k</mi></math> for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"r\"><mi>r</mi></math> in&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus h right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y minus k right parenthesis squared equals r squared\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>h</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mi>k</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mi>r</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math> yields <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus 16 right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y minus 17 right parenthesis squared equals left parenthesis 7 k right parenthesis squared\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mn>7</mn><mi>k</mi><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus 16 right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y minus 17 right parenthesis squared equals 49 k squared\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>49</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>. Therefore, the equation that represents this circle is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus 16 right parenthesis squared plus left parenthesis y minus 17 right parenthesis squared equals 49 k squared\"><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>16</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><msup><mrow><mo>(</mo><mi>y</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>17</mn><mo>)</mo></mrow><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>=</mo><mn>49</mn><msup><mi>k</mi><mn>2</mn></msup></math>.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">Choice A is incorrect. This equation represents a circle with radius&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"7 StartRoot k EndRoot\"><mn>7</mn><msqrt><mi>k</mi></msqrt></math>, not&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"7 k\"><mn>7</mn><mi>k</mi></math>.</p>\n<p st